This paper deals with the task of Question Answering using neural models, which falls under the sub-category of Natural Language Processing (NLP) in Computer Science. Specifically, the paper focuses on the Stanford Question Answering Dataset (SQuAD), which is a popular benchmark dataset for NLP research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
